#PressPlay: Get y’all popcorn ready, Chance the Rapper’s new movie drops today in theaters across the country! “Chance the Rapper’s Magnificent Coloring World” marks the first time an artist has independently distributed a film to theatres.
________
“Magnificent Coloring World” is a concert film self-distributed through Chance the Rapper’s House of Kicks production company and film house.
________
Chance wrote, produced, edited and starred in the film, working hard this past year to bring never-before-seen footage to his fans. The footage was filmed in 2017 right before Chance took home 3 Grammys for his critically acclaimed mixtape “Coloring Book.”
________
Fans will be able to see the film in person for a limited time in several cities including Los Angeles, New York, Chicago, Detori, Las Vegas and Philly.

node.title: Chance The Rapper’s Film Released Today

#TSRLivingLarge: OHKAY! #TheWeeknd is out here living grand and in style, at least according to his recent real estate purchase! The artist reportedly bought a Bel Air mega-mansion in “one of the largest deals closed in Los Angeles so far this year.” 
_______________________________
According to @wsj, The Weeknd dropped a hefty $70 million on the approximately 33,000-square-foot home— that wasn’t even on the market! To compare, his previous home in the Hidden Hills was sold to Madonna in April for only $19.3 million. 
_______________________________
His new Bel Air beauty was previously owned by Dutch celebrities who purchased it back in 2015 for only $21.4 million. Over three years, they modernized their place with curated pieces from around the world. 
_______________________________
The star will enjoy amenities like an indoor pool, spa with a sauna, outdoor infinity pool with a waterfall, movie theater, gym, sports court and music studio sitting on 1.3 acres of private land. (SWIPE) to take a peek inside his personal paradise! 👏🏾

Whew! #Roommates, #BritneySpears is facing a new challenge amid the legal battle to be released from her conservatorship. According to @people, the artist is under investigation by a California sheriff’s department for allegedly striking a female housekeeper. At this time, Britney is only a suspect in the alleged misdemeanor battery incident. 
_______________________________
Captain Eric Buschow of Ventura County Sheriff’s Department told People that an employee reported Britney after she allegedly “struck them during a dispute.” The incident reportedly took place inside the star’s home. 
_______________________________
The captain did not share specifics about the case, but confirmed that misdemeanor battery involves “physical contact” with someone else. Despite reports, a source close to Britney painted a different picture to People.
_______________________________
The undisclosed source said there was no hitting. Britney allegedly “tried to knock” her cell phone out of the housekeeper’s hand. However, no injuries were reported following the incident. Thoughts, #Roomies? (📸: @gettyimages)

TSR Staff: Cassandra S. @__casmarie

Nine Black protesters will be receiving $500 each from a former ice cream shop owner who violated their civil rights. According to @apnews, a lawsuit filed by the state alleged that #DavidElmendorf called 911 with false accusations against peaceful protesters — calling them “savages.” Now, David is facing permanent legal consequences in addition to the  $4,500 payout.

“There is zero tolerance for harassment, intimidation, or violence of any kind against anyone in New York,” New York Attorney General Letitia James said in a prepared release.
_______________________________
The state’s lawsuit accused David of “threatening and harassing” the protesters and because they were peacefully assembling, his actions were a violation of their rights.
_______________________________
